    4894      224075 : static void adjust_frame_for_plc(struct ast_channel *chan, struct ast_frame *frame, struct ast_datastore *datastore)

    4898             : 
    4899             :         /* As a general note, let me explain the somewhat odd calculations used when taking
    4900             :          * the frame offset into account here. According to documentation in frame.h, the frame's
    4901             :          * offset field indicates the number of bytes that the audio is offset. The plc->samples_buf
    4902             :          * is not an array of bytes, but rather an array of 16-bit integers since it holds SLIN
    4903             :          * samples. So I had two choices to make here with the offset.
    4904             :          *
    4905             :          * 1. Make the offset AST_FRIENDLY_OFFSET bytes. The main downside for this is that
    4906             :          *    I can't just add AST_FRIENDLY_OFFSET to the plc->samples_buf and have the pointer
    4907             :          *    arithmetic come out right. I would have to do some odd casting or division for this to
    4908             :          *    work as I wanted.
    4909             :          * 2. Make the offset AST_FRIENDLY_OFFSET * 2 bytes. This allows the pointer arithmetic
    4910             :          *    to work out better with the plc->samples_buf. The downside here is that the buffer's
    4911             :          *    allocation contains an extra 64 bytes of unused space.
    4912             :          *
    4913             :          * I decided to go with option 2. This is why in the calloc statement and the statement that
    4914             :          * sets the frame's offset, AST_FRIENDLY_OFFSET is multiplied by 2.
    4915             :          */
    4916             :
